Class BoxArena

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.github.mdsimmo.bomberman.arenas.BoxArena
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Arena, org.bukkit.configuration.serialization.ConfigurationSerializable

    public class BoxArena
extends Object
implements Arena
    A basic implementation of an arena. This implementation only knows how to handle structures bound by a single box region.

      • createArena

        public static void createArena(String name,
                               Box box,
                               Arena.Callback callback)
        Defines a new arena. The method will schedule a background task to create the new arena over several ticks.
        Parameters:
        name - the name of the new arena. If an arena with the same name already existed, then it will be overridden
        box - the box to define the new arena from
        callback - gives the created arena back
